    <stitle>FAN DRIVE CLUTCH: HORTON ON/OFF - REASSEMBLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="2">
        <title>REASSEMBLE</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1200415">Figure 22</hotlnk>for all item number callouts in parentheses unless otherwise
            noted.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1200415" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1200422" filename="../figg12/G1200422.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 22. Fan Clutch - Exploded View</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. JOURNAL FOR SHEAVE BEARINGS (2)</callout1>
                <callout1>2. SHEAVE BEARINGS (2)</callout1>
                <callout1>3. BEARING SPACER (2) (INNER AND OUTER)</callout1>
                <callout1>4. SHEAVE</callout1>
                <callout1>5. FRICTION FACING (DISC)</callout1>
                <callout1>6. TORX BUTTON HEAD CAPSCREW</callout1>
                <callout1>7. JOURNAL SPACER</callout1>
                <callout1>8. HUB BEARINGS (2) FRONT/REAR</callout1>
                <callout1>9. BEARING SPACER</callout1>
                <callout1>10. HUB (SPLINED) (PISTON)</callout1>
                <callout1>11. PISTON FRICTION (DISC)</callout1>
                <callout1>12. PISTON ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>13. O-RING (LARGE)</callout1>
                <callout1>14. LOCK NUT</callout1>
                <callout1>15. U-CAP</callout1>
                <callout1>16. CARTRIDGE</callout1>
                <callout1>17. RETAINING RING</callout1>
                <callout1>18. CARTRIDGE ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>19. FACE SEAL</callout1>
                <callout1>20. O-RING (SMALL)</callout1>
                <callout1>21. AIR CHAMBER ASSEMBLY (INCLUDES ITEM 19 FACE SEAL)</callout1>
                <callout1>22. HEX SOCKET HEAD CAPSCREW</callout1>
                <callout1>23. STUD BOLT</callout1>
                <callout1>24. LOCKWASHER</callout1>
                <callout1>25. HEX NUT</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide sheave (Item 4) onto mounting (journal) bracket (Item 1).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install journal spacer (Item 7).</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Journal spacer lip must face up or towards the front of clutch (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1200423">Figure 23</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f1200423" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1200423" filename="../figg12/G1200423.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 23. Positioning Journal Spacer</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. LIP MUST FACE UP</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. JOURNAL SPACER</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide splined hub onto mounting (journal) bracket.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Replace and tighten adjusting nut (Item 14,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1200415">Figure 22</hotlnk>) to 150 ft-lbs. (203 N&#8226;m).
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Some fan clutch models may contain a special adjusting nut and lockwasher. Discard these items
                        and replace with a self-locking adjusting nut (Item 14).
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide piston/friction disc onto splined hub.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Replace air chamber (Item 21).</para>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Care must be exercised when replacing air chamber to avoid damage to O-rings.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install and tighten socket head capscrews (Item 22) to 180 in-lbs. (20.3 N&#8226;m).</para>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>If the fan clutch contains lockwashers with capscrews (Item 22), the lockwashers must be
                        re-used.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
